<div id="review_1818018193" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1818018193" />
    <a title="Robert Palmer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3877218-robert-palmer"><img alt="Robert Palmer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1534546789p2/3877218.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1818018193?book_show_action=true">Nov 28, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robert Palmer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robert Palmer" href="/user/show/3877218-robert-palmer">Robert Palmer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3877218-robert-palmer?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1818018193" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9212071440200927717">Allen drury&apos;s Advise and Consent is a Pulitzer Prize winning novel,the title comes from the United States Constitution which provides that the President of the United States &quot; shall nominate and by and with the advise and consent of the Senate shall appoint Ambassador&apos;s,Judges of the Supreme Court and other officers of the United States.<br/>This novel is a fictional account of the nomination of a prominent liberal,Robert Leffingwell,to the position of Secretary of State during the Cold War with Russ</span>
  <span id="freeText9212071440200927717" style="display:none">Allen drury's Advise and Consent is a Pulitzer Prize winning novel,the title comes from the United States Constitution which provides that the President of the United States " shall nominate and by and with the advise and consent of the Senate shall appoint Ambassador's,Judges of the Supreme Court and other officers of the United States.<br />This novel is a fictional account of the nomination of a prominent liberal,Robert Leffingwell,to the position of Secretary of State during the Cold War with Russia.<br />Leffingwell is a highly controversial person and a group of Senators are dead sent against Leffingwell, others are equivocal,some are unsure.<br />Throughout the novel the various Senators are known as the Majority or the Minorty and the words " Democrat and Republican"are never used in this novel,although there are a few empty headed liberals and embittered conservatives<br />In 1959 when this book was published I was just getting discharged after four years in the Navy and the only politicians I knew of was President Eisenhower and Richard J Daley of Chicago and I wasn't much concerned about what was going on in the rest of the world and if I had tried to read this book I wouldn't have gotten beyond ten pages, I was just having fun. I went to a party in 1959 but the party was over in 1968 when the Democratic national convention was held in Chicago and it seemed as though the whole fabric of America was coming undone and the party was most definitely over for me,I finally grew up and became an adult.<br />While reading this novel I was reminded of the miracle at Philadelphia and the Constitutional Convention in 1787,a speech at Gettysburg,WWI,WWII and I still have high hopes for the future.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9212071440200927717" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


